caption: Outstanding vibe. Great retro diner. The food and service was great.  Will definitely come back.
Super friendly staff. Nostalgic place with great food.

The staff was very friendly and we enjoyed our lunch here. There was a lot of history on the walls and we played trivia pursuit at the table while we waited for our food. There are trivia pursuit cards at every table. There's a good variety on the menu. You won't be disappointed.

Walked into this Cafe and was immediately met with happy and friendly staff. Love the old vintage theme, and food is absolutely delicious. I got the chicken and fries, while my girlfriend got the burger and onion rings.  Absolutely worth it!

Drink specials daily, including the $5 Mai Tai.  Super fun atmosphere, playing old music videos, and they have a huge selection of vintage finds for sale, Coca-Cola, Elvis memorabilia, comic books, I Love Lucy, old Barbies, Hawaii- 5 0, autographed photos, and just so much more.  Great for gift shopping too.  You can play pinball on a Wizard of Oz machine, and classic Pac Man and Donkey Kong.

This is an Americana memorabilia gem. It's decor covers all manner of popular television, movie, and pop culture flavors primarily from the 50s - 70s but also beyond on both directions. There is a loop of classic TV theme songs and musical clips from movies (Elvis is featured prominently). Quite entertaining. Happy hour was nice with $5 tropical drinks and $3 drafts. We had an assortment of diner fried classics and they were very good. All in all, a super fun experience!
Love this spot! Definitely worth going!

I absolutely love this place, been coming here for years! The people working are fabulous and there's so many things to look at. The food is quick and delicious. One of my favorite parts is all the memorabilia that they have all along the walls. Definitely would recommend this place to others especially if you like retro stuff.
American food ,pizza was delicious and happy hour drinks , can buy vintage old stuff just so cool !

Had a great dinner here last night. The place is set up like a vintage 50's diner full of elvis memorabilia, old arcade games and other vintage items. It's a great place to eat as you get to look at all the decor whilst you do so. The food is pretty great too, myself and my girlfriend got a milkshake each (as you would in a diner), with a chili cheese dog, a Hula burger and a side of fries for main. The milkshakes are amazing and the bonus was that she made so much, we got the extra so basically a second drink free. The chili dog and burger were great, just found them to be a little in the small side. The fires however were quite large, deffinately able to share between 2. Great experience, great staff/owners, great food. Highly recommend this place.

When we saw this restaurant it reminded me of the restaurants in Las Vegas. This restaurant serves American Food, and drink menu that will take you way back when the root beer became popular in USA. I had the "Scooby-Doo" Hot Dog, which is a Pizza hot dog, and oh boy that hot dog had lots of yummy marinara sauce and the perfect ratio of pepperoni & parmesan cheese.  Ask for a fork and a knife cuz you will need it. Among all the memorabilia that is for sale. The place has a ouside view to a very busy street. You may also play trivia while you wait for your delicious meal. Did I mention the music? They play a variety of music videos from the 50's, 60's... and today's. Come and check it out, your favorite celebrity memorabilia might be here.

We got the hula bopper burger, and it's not a big slice of fried pineapple, it's pineapple chunks and chopped ham like is in a salad. Still, I thought it tasted good, though my husband didn't like the sauce. Shakes were good, cheese fries could use more flavor. Fun atmosphere though that plays clips from old movies.

Stay away from this place! It is basically a giant advertisement gone awry. The restaurant looks cool and has a very 1950's feel. There is a lot od memorabilia available to look at and purchase, some of it for decent prices. However the dining aspect leaves much to be desired. The serving staff was rude and terse, cutting off our drink order to tell us we have to order at the counter, after we were sat and given menus. Three employees (and possibly the manager) sat and watched me write down all our orders and bring it up to THEM. The food was decent but overpriced, and while paying the check the manager hovered over the pinpad pressuring us to leave a tip. And to make it worse, the $100 we spent buying merchandise was factored into the tip amount. They wanted to sucker us into paying a tip for OUR shopping as well as for the "service" they provided which was at best no service and at worst downright disrespectful. Best to avoid this one altogether. There's a lovely Burger King a few feet away where you can get the same quality food and better service.

Awesome place to check out. Lots to see. The burgers and fries weren't the best I had but the prices were good for Waikiki. The ice cream is awesome, tho.
Very good interior decor and a good place to hang out. Food is ok.

The diner itself was awesome. My boyfriend and I stopped in to look around and take advantage of their happy hour. All of our servers were great and friendly. We finished out first round and as we were ordering a second. A woman came and stopped our server. My boyfriend had a couple sips left of his drink and this woman (later found to be the manager) refused to make him another one until he was completely done. She did not smile. Was extremely rude and had a negative demeanor. We had another drink and left. Every time we spoke to a server etc. the manager would stare us down and it was very uncomfortable. We handed a tip to one of our servers and she almost seemed frightened. Stating last time someone tried to give her a tip her manager took it away. We went to pay at the front and the manager was starring at us from across the diner. We placed the tip in the jar only hoping it gets to our servers. Awesome place but the manager totally killed the vibe and cut our visit short with her negative attitude.
Food is just ok, not worth the high prices.
50's style diner. Mostly a burgers and sandwich joint. The food is good. The ambience is great. Nice place to eat and unwind. Ate there twice.

(Translated by Google) The store promotion is amazing. Different from Japan's retro, it embodies a unique American retro feeling throughout the store. It was a wonderful space where a general store and a restaurant were successfully fused. I learned how to stick to the concept.  (Original) 店のプロモーションがすごい。日本のレトロとはまた違う、アメリカ独特のレトロ感を店内のいたるところで体現しています。雑貨屋と飲食店が見事にフュージョンする素敵な空間でした。コンセプトを貫き通す姿勢が勉強になりました。

The place itself looks fairly nice in the mold of being a 50s style diner with there being lots of memorabilia (albeit some of it cheesy and/or not really 50s stuff), but everything else about the place was subpar.  The prices were somewhat high to begin with, and the food did not warrant such prices, especially the deserts (10 bucks for a plain brownie sundae with two scoops of ice cream and nothing special about it).  The Hawaiian Pizza my wife and I ordered had cracker like crust and was a rather plain pizza.  The food was served Luke warm and was cold before we could finish it.  The waitress who served us was brief and aloof.  My wife asked for her food to be boxed, and not only did the waitress not box the food for her, but she brought out a piece of tin foil instead that was too small to use.  Who does that?  I never have seen a restaurant not have a box before.  We asked for more tin foil, and we never received it after about 10 minutes, so we asked again about the tin foil.  The waitress acted like we were inconveniencing or annoying her with our request we had made 10 minutes prior.  The bill without alcohol ended up being about the same for a much higher quality restaurant with alcohol.  Upon leaving, my wife had to use the restroom, and all they had was an access code to a restroom that was located in an outdoor shopping center that had mold on the sink.  The hot water didn't work either.
This place was okay. The food was good but there was a mix up in the kitchen and our food wasn't actually put in when we ordered so it took quite some time for it to come out.
Great burger and crispy fries.
Interesting atmosphere. Satisfied our pizza craving for a reasonable price.
Loved the food and interior, will be back next year!
Cool decor! That's about it.... food seemed "generic". No bathroom.
Great place. Lots of Old America memorabilia. Food is great too. James Bond 007 Pizza rocked.
Food was good and a good price. Kids liked the atmosphere of the restaurant.
The shakes are hella expensive but hella worth it. Burgers are not bad either.
Average food, there are better spots nearby.
Is a good choose
Good casual dining place for reasonable price.  I had the 1/3 lb burger with chili and it was very good.  The fries, chili and deserts are also very good.

I have been to Waikiki several times over the past few years. Rock Island is one of the places I visit each time. It reminds me of diners from when I was a child. It is a nice place in which to sit and relax and reminisce about old times. Definitely a contrast to the other busy locales on Waikiki. I definitely recommend the milk shakes.
Fun restaurant with 50's theme. Pizza was ok nothing to rave about. Memorabilia is great and many items for sale. Trivia cards on table. Great restaurant for families.
So much fun!!!!!!!!!!
Its a 50's style american restaurant. Really basic kind of food like burgers, seams to be a blast from the past. Food is alright, but not top notch.
(Translated by Google) Superb! It has remained in my heart, one of the best memories of the trip to Oahu!  (Original) Stupendo! Mi è rimasto nel cuore, uno dei ricordi più belli del viaggio a Oahu!

Had to write this after going there 3 times, & seeing the negative reviews here. I must say that this diner is in the heart of Waikiki-where a simple burger can easily cost 12.00.  I went 3 times-the decor is fantastic, the service was great every time, and the food was not only good, it was priced well below the competition. I have absolutely no complaints & would not only recommend going-I would go back in a heartbeat.

We visited Rock Island twice. The first time was when we first arrived in Waikiki as we were just scoping out the local food scene, The owner was very chatty and polite at the time and we said we would come back to eat while we were in Waikiki. Well, we did go back, BIG MISTAKE!! The owner totally ignored us when we walked in so  we just sat at a table, ordered a couple of drinks then proceeded to be constantly pressured by the waitress to order food, It seemed we just weren't allowed to sit and enjoy a drink while we decided on what to order. In the end I ordered a burger and fries just to get her off our backs! When the burger eventually came out, it was swimming in some sort of liquid, Yuk! After about 15 mins, the owner came over and bluntly asked if we would be ordering ice cream. When I replied no, the unfinished basket of fries I was still eating was whipped away and the check was thrown on the table (we didn't even ask for it) by the owner, who didn't even bother to ask if everything was ok, as he turned his back and walked away. We will be going back to Waikiki soon but we will give Rock Island a wide berth and we have told everyone we know who is going to Hawaii to do the same!! The owner is a douchbag!
Great atmosphere, good friendly service, good food!
